commits.message: Update dev dependencies; update lint rules

Update react version; fix character creation flow

- Update React to stable version 16.8.3
- Fix skill display bug, ensuring properly formatted names display over keys
- Fix skill sourcing bug, allowing classes like the bard to source 3 skills from the full list as intended without requiring the list defined upfront
- Update remaining areas depending on CLASSES object that is now a map instead of an array
Update react-native-progress; fix tests
Update remaining dependencies; prep for expo upgrade

Upgade to expo SDK 36

- Update jest to use absolute paths for mocks
- Add unimodules-permisisons-interface to transformIgnorePatterns
- Update styles for flex containers and items in cards for ability
scores and hitpoints
- Update height of list items for languages
- Suppress warnings for pending changes to react-native-material-ui for
deprecated lifecycle methods; update any existing uses in app that are
no longer needed

commits.message:
Upgade to expo SDK 36

- Update jest to use absolute paths for mocks
- Add unimodules-permisisons-interface to transformIgnorePatterns
- Update styles for flex containers and items in cards for ability
scores and hitpoints
- Update height of list items for languages
- Suppress warnings for pending changes to react-native-material-ui for
deprecated lifecycle methods; update any existing uses in app that are
no longer needed
Update remaining dependencies; prep for expo upgrade
Update react-native-progress; fix tests

Update react version; fix character creation flow

- Update React to stable version 16.8.3
- Fix skill display bug, ensuring properly formatted names display over keys
- Fix skill sourcing bug, allowing classes like the bard to source 3 skills from the full list as intended without requiring the list defined upfront
- Update remaining areas depending on CLASSES object that is now a map instead of an array

issue.title: Update component lifecycle methods
issue.body: Some lifecycle methods are no longer deemed safe. This requires uplifting some of the dependencies that used to rely on them, i.e. seeing if they have workarounds in place before it becomes a hard stop in React 17+ or moving to other solutions.

issue.title: Move to new key-value storage solution
issue.body: Simple store uses unlinked new location and expo does not support it. Consider moving to expo's secure key-value storage solution or selecting another one.

issue.title: Fix list display issue in character background selection screen
issue.body: Bulleted list item is offset by a bit on next line due to text overflow (improper newline placement?).

pull_request.title: Bump tar from 2.2.1 to 2.2.2
pull_request.body:
Bumps [tar](https://github.com/npm/node-tar) from 2.2.1 to 2.2.2.
Commits - [`523c5c7`](https://github.com/npm/node-tar/commit/523c5c7fef48b10811fccd12b42803c61b6aead8) 2.2.2 - [`7ecef07`](https://github.com/npm/node-tar/commit/7ecef07da6a9e72cc0c4d0c9c6a8e85b6b52395d) Bump fstream to fix hardlink overwriting vulnerability - [`9fc84b9`](https://github.com/npm/node-tar/commit/9fc84b9c596c3589d4c1ab050843de0eafb002e8) Use {} for hardlink tracking instead of [] - [`15e59f1`](https://github.com/npm/node-tar/commit/15e59f1d671ffbe4ae7c74dafcbec93ea2584e34) Only track previously seen hardlinks - [`4f85851`](https://github.com/npm/node-tar/commit/4f8585178af78f8f64c5ca38e923c306613278b9) Ignore potentially unsafe files - See full diff in [compare view](https://github.com/npm/node-tar/compare/v2.2.1...v2.2.2)
